CIDR: classless Interdomain routing
YAML: yet another markup language (html/xml)
JSON: JavaScript Object Notation

{
  "Version": "2012-10-17",
  "Statement": [
    {
      "Sid": "AllowSpecificIPReadOnly",
      "Effect": "Allow",
      "Principal": "*",
      "Action": "s3:GetObject",
      "Resource": "arn:aws:s3:::my-bucket-name/*",
      "Condition": {
        "IpAddress": {
          "aws:SourceIp": "203.0.113.0/24"
        }
      }
    }
  ]
}

s - sid - statement identifier - read only 
p - principal - who all/user/entity/"*" - public access
e - effect - allow/deny the action
a - action - get object in s3/download
r - resource - s3 / "*" everything in that bucket
c - condition - extra filtering / from specific IP address
